&lt;p>A standalone ES setup for data storage inevitably faces two issues: massive data storage and single point of failure.&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Massive data storage&lt;/strong>: Logically split the index into N shards, storing them across multiple nodes.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Single point of failure&lt;/strong>: Back up shard data on different nodes (replicas).&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
